faceoff_positive.comments:
Okay, so I've had time to use it, knowing that it would take longer than the trial time to show the full improvements it's meant to give but I've been able to assess quite a bit since I'm a skincare fan and know my way around the good and bad.

First off, this has all the markers of high end. The smell, the bottle, the feel of the product itself are all what you expect from top quality brands. The bottle is smooth and durable and the pump is sleek and easy to distribute just the amount you need. It didn't take long to figure out that amount. It's very potent stuff so go easy on it. It absorbs well and doesn't leave behind a thick feeling or visible residue.

Which brings me to why I didn't give it five stars. You have to be really careful not to get it too close to the eye. This isn't something that you can just close your eyes and rub over the lid. It irritated my eye and needed to be washed off to reapply when I did that, but luckily, it does solve the problem. I also noticed that it can irritate or cause a burning sensation if you sweat so I'd stick to only using the contour before bed and in the morning only when you know you won't be active. Like I said, it can be rinsed away and reapplied to clean soothed skin once dry. 

I'm used to retinol eye creams so this is nothing to new for me but for those not used to potent eye creams, go very small on the amount, keep it away from the lash line and mind that sweat can alter the pH and cause sensitivity. Otherwise, it does feel comparable to very effective eye creams I've used before. Generally, I tone and moisturize first to make eye creams less irritating. A lot of people that have negative results don't realize it's important to prep your clean skin and do this step last.

And I feel like I should add, definitely not for very young skin. I've seen a recent trend in children getting expensive anti-aging skin care products that can do harm and even permanently damage. This is one of those that is clearly meant for mature skin that can handle stronger chemicals. Even adults should be properly prepping to tolerate strong ingredients though.
faceoff_positive.headline: Strong so always prep skin first

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received the Exuviance Total 360 Eye Cream free from Exuviance in exchange for my honest review. I loved that this cream is not fragranced and when used as directed there was very little sensitivity. 
I received and used these products for 30 days. I did not see improvement in any of my fine lines or wrinkles or any firming of the skin. Past experience with antiaging products would say that I probably need a little more time to see any true effectiveness. I have normal skin that leans more dry. I found that this cream did not provide a ton of moisture. Therefore, it didn't play very well under make up. If you have more of an oily skin situation going on, you may love these products. If you are more dry this may be a no go for you. This will not be a product that I will be re-purchasing. Bonus points for the cute packaging.
faceoff_negative.headline: Fast absorbing not much moisture
